import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['departure_delay'].hist(bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['departure_delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['departure_delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['departure_delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['departure_delay'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['flight_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['flight_time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['flight_time'] = data['flight_time'].dt.hour + data['flight_time'].dt.minute/60
    avg_flight_time = data.groupby('airline')['flight_time'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_flight_time['airline'], avg_flight_time['flight_time'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Airline')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Flight Time (hours)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average flight time for different airlines?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    hour_counts = data.groupby('hour').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.plot(hour_counts['hour'], hour_counts['counts'])
    plt.axvline(hour_counts['hour'].iloc[hour_counts['counts'].idxmax()], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Busiest hour: {hour_counts['hour'].iloc[hour_counts['counts'].idxmax()]:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the busiest time of day for flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = data['distance'].astype(float)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['distance'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():0.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['arrival_delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['arrival_delay'], errors='coerce')
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['arrival_delay', 'distance'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['arrival_delay'], alpha=0.2)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Arrival Delay')
    ax.axhline(y=data['arrival_delay'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Arrival Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['arrival_delay'].median()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the relationship between flight distance and arrival delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
